introduction: Nathan EarnestNoble provides an overview of quantum hardware and its essential components, including superconducting qubits, circuit quantum electrodynamics, and device errors. He discusses the impact of external loops, gate errors, and shock errors on quantum process tomography and shares resources for further learning.

sections.title: Section 1: Superconducting Qubits and Circuit Quantum Electrodynamics
content: Explanation of superconducting qubits and their role in quantum computing.
Introduction to circuit quantum electrodynamics as the paradigm used to realize quantum computers at IBM.
Discussion of external loops and their potential impact on quantum process tomography.
Overview of different superconducting qubit architectures, such as transmon qubits, tunable transmons, fluxoniums, and zero-pi qubits.

sections.title: Section 2: Device Errors and Error Mitigation Strategies
content: Explanation of different device errors, including gate errors, spam errors, and shock errors.
Discussion of the impact of these errors on quantum process tomography and state preparation.
Overview of resources for measuring coupling strength between qubits and mitigating errors.
Introduction to quantum process tomography and its role in measuring the state of qubits.
